    "A CT does not accurately describe an actual conspiracy.",
    "Secondly, Barkun [2] distinguishes CTs into three categories: event, systemic, and super conspiracy.",
    "Event conspiracies account for particular events, such as the Kennedy murder [3].",
    "Systemic conspiracies have wide-reaching aims to dominate nations or regions, such as those blamed on Jews, Masons, or capitalists.",
    "Super conspiracies link multiple conspiracies in a hierarchical order, with an allegedly secret and powerful evil force at the apex."
